; ============================================================================
; INBOUND WHITELIST -- who is allowed to call this PBX.
;
; !!! SECURITY NOTE !!!
; This file defaults to "*" (allow all) so inbound test calls work without
; any extra config. ONCE you have a paid DID and care about spam/robocalls,
; DELETE the "*" line and add specific E.164 numbers below. Otherwise this
; PBX will ring on every junk call that hits your DID.
;
; Format: one E.164 number per line, matched against the inbound caller-ID
; (CallerID(num)) presented by Telnyx. Example: +15125551234
;
; Rules:
;   - ";" starts a comment. Everything after ";" on a line is ignored.
;     Label numbers with names:
;         +15125551234   ; Mom mobile
;         +18005551212   ; doctor's office
;   - Lines that are entirely whitespace or comment are ignored.
;   - A single "*" on its own line means "allow ANY caller". Useful when
;     you first get a DID and aren't sure who'll legitimately call you.
;   - The token "anonymous" matches calls that arrive without caller-ID
;     (privacy=anonymous or empty From). Add it explicitly if you want to
;     accept those; otherwise they're blocked.
;   - Empty file = NO inbound calls accepted.
;
; Edits take effect on the NEXT call -- no reload needed.
; ============================================================================

; Allow everything by default. Comment this line out and add specific
; numbers below once you want to filter.
*  ; allow-all sentinel -- delete or comment to start filtering

; Examples:
; +15125551234   ; Mom
; +18005551212   ; pharmacy
; anonymous      ; allow calls with hidden caller-ID

